snippet: Serena Williams, 31, moved within a victory of becoming the oldest top-ranked women’s player, sweeping aside Urszula Radwanska to reach the quarterfinals of the Qatar Open in Doha.
abstract: Serena Williams moves within one victory of becoming oldest top-ranked women’s tennis player, reaching quarterfinals of Qatar Open in Doha.
lead_paragraph: Serena Williams, 31, moved within a victory of becoming the oldest top-ranked women’s player, sweeping aside Urszula Radwanska to reach the quarterfinals of the Qatar Open in Doha.
